@Nick, "<br/>
"Consumer spending is 70% of the economy and consumers are the key." this is exactly the problem. NO nation can survive by making the consumer 70% of GDP. Where does the money come from? 25 million out of work, low wages, NO INTEREST on savings, and yet, folks like you believe that this is a sustainable means of running the "world's biggest economy". It used to be that manufacturing carried the burden, but it has shifted to consumption to keep people in hock, pay high interest on their credit cards, the rich have gotten one helluva lot richer, and poor--well MITT doesn't really care about the poor, they will take care of themselves.<br/>
  It is totally insane to suppose that we can actually survive on producing nothing, the new jobs are "mow and blow", and where is the money coming from?. Pay me interest on my savings and I'll likely spend it--but no interest guarantees NO SPENDING FOR THE DURATION.
